      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KUALIGHT (2) had been building towards another win and she achieved it at this circuit and distance last week, coming from a wider barrier and getting home by 1.2 metres. Has the benefit of a good draw so could strike again. VIEW THE ART (1) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when third from a much wider barrier at this circuit and distance. That was in a higher-graded race than this so the combinations of a class drop and the ace draw could see her back in the winners' list. NO ALIBI NZ (6) missed by a head here two back then atoned with a fighting win after working from this barrier at Young last week. Go well again. SPIRIT OF SAHARA (9) had a tough barrier at Shepparton last start but draws for a nice trail here and scored a win at this circuit and distance two back.",
